As Cody crept forward, he addressed Lulu in a whisper. “Do you remember the one time we tried exploring a place like this as a family?” He chuckled. “I don't think there was a moment in which at least one of us wasn't at someone else's throat.” He considered that briefly. “Literally, at one point. Serves me right for trying to take that dire wombat corpse from you, I suppose. I would have let you have the meat, you know.” Lulu looked away, her aloof air somewhat spoiled by her frantically waving tail.
